**Courie****r/Administrative Assistant**
**Level II (1.0 FTE)**  

**Central Office**  





**Qualifications****:**
+ Strong interpersonal, communication, and organizational skills;
+ Ability to follow directions and work with a minimum of supervisor direction;
+ Valid Connecticut driver’s license;
+ Experience in mailroom and delivery procedures;
+ Ability to interact with school staff;
+ Ability to lift and carry weights between 25 to 75 pounds, and work in poor weather conditions including heat, cold, rain, and snow
+ Computer skills required: Microsoft Office Suite

**Duties****:**
+ Provide daily secretarial duties to the Human Resources Department (60% of job responsibilities)
+ Run the centralized mailroom function for Central Office and all schools;
+ Sort, deliver, and post all mail and parcels throughout the Westport School System, and, as appropriate, to members of the Board of Education, Board of Finance, and Representative Town Meeting (overtime required);
+ Coordinate large mailings and bulk mailings from all areas of the Westport school system;
+ Responsible for maintenance and supplies for central office copier and mailroom equipment;
+ Perform daily errands, tasks, and assume such other responsibilities as assigned;
+ Maintain employee staff room including cleaning of appliances;
+ Organize and maintain vault archive records;
+ Take new employee photo and create I.D. badge and send to appropriate school;
+ Responsible for copying projects as needed;




**Salary Range****:** According to the Secretary contract  

 (see website www.westportps.org/employment – personnel contracts)  



**Starting Date**: As Soon as Possible or Mutually Agreed Upon Date  



**Application Deadline****:** The position is open until filled.  

 **Application Procedures:**  



**Internal applicants** must submit an online application through the Westport Public Schools website. **Job # 1961** (Please be sure to select internal applicant. This signifies one’s current status as a Westport employee.)  



**External applicants** must submit an online application through the Westport Public Schools website. **Job # 1961** (Paper copies will not be accepted.)  



***The Westport Board of Education will not make employment decision (including decisions related to hiring, assignment, compensation, promotion, demotion, disciplinary action and termination) on the basis of race, color, religion, age, sex, marital status, sexual orientation, national origin, ancestry, disability (including pregnancy), genetic information, veteran status or gender identity or expression, except in the case of a bona fide occupational qualification.***

**About JCRC-NY**

The Jewish Community Relations Council of New York (JCRC-NY), a proud UJA-Federation of NY agency, serves as the primary community relations agency for the Jewish community in the metropolitan New York area. As an active force in New York civic and communal life, JCRC-NY operates as a central coordinating and resource body to: (1) Be a common table to cultivate understanding and joint action amongst diverse groups within the Jewish community; (2) Cultivate deeper relationships with the broader New York community to address critical issues and engender a shared society; (3) Ensure the security of the Jewish community in the face of rising antisemitism; and (4) Foster increased understanding and appreciation for the Jewish community’s relationship with Israel among diverse groups of New Yorkers. Under new leadership, JCRC-NY seeks to intensify its community relations efforts, strengthen existing partnerships and build new relationships with diverse leaders in our city to advance the values, interests and security of the New York Jewish community and build a more interconnected New York for all.

**The Position**

JCRC-NY seeks an innovative and driven Social Media and Communications Manager who is passionate about our work with proven ability to articulate – both in writing and verbally – our activities and positions in a cohesive and compelling voice to our audiences, including leaders of Jewish and other faith communities, public officials, diverse community leaders, and the general public. The Manager is experienced in communicating across various media and social media platforms and is able to manage projects in regular coordination with staff across the agency. This position is full-time (40 hours per week) and requires working some evenings and weekends (Sundays) throughout the year. JCRC-NY has a hybrid work schedule and requires that employee’s work a minimum of three days per week in the office. The Social Media and Communications Manager reports to the Chief Executive Officer, and must be based in the New York metropolitan area.

**Responsibilities include:**

* Managing and generating content for JCRC-NY’s social media accounts on a daily basis (Facebook, X, YouTube, Instagram) and establishing and increasing followings and engagement on each platform;
* Creating and scheduling a calendar of social media posts, monitoring social media channels, and responding to external users where appropriate;
* Managing and updating the JCRC-NY website;
* Managing JCRC-NY’s mass email communication software and using it to create, populate, and disseminate relevant content and messaging;
* Planning, developing, and implementing all activities relating to communications and aligning all external communications to the organization's unique voice;
* Consulting with staff to identify and write stories/articles of interest to share through the media, social media, website and other platforms;
* Identifying and cultivating relationships with key media contacts and social media influencers, proactively reaching out and informing them of JCRC-NY activities and areas of expertise;
* Serving as point of contact for and managing external communications and digital media consultants
* Engaging in other aspects of JCRC-NY’s work as needed.

**Requirements**

* Bachelor’s degree with 2-4 years’ experience or Master’s degree with 1-3 years’ experience in communications, social media, and content production;
* Excellent written, verbal and interpersonal communication skills;
* Significant attention to detail and accuracy, with an ability to manage multiple and competing priorities simultaneously;
* Strong familiarity and experience working with a variety of social networks, including X, Facebook, Instagram, YouTube, and other platforms, including backend software and tools to generate quality content and evaluate success;
* Familiarity with managing and updating WordPress-based or similar websites;
* Familiarity with the diversity of the New York Jewish Community and the societal and political issues affecting New Yorkers;
* Knowledge of current affairs concerning Israel and global Jewish affairs;
* A strong capacity with Microsoft Outlook, Word, Excel and PowerPoint applications and Google-Suite (mail, drive, docs, calendar, and sheets);
* Ability to work with graphics and familiarity with Canva, HTML, Publisher, Illustrator, Photoshop Adobe Acrobat and basic video editing skills;
* Experience using social media and email marketing platforms for development is a plus;
* Nonprofit or government experience a plus.

**Compensation**

* $70,000-$80,000, depending on experience
* Benefits package, paid vacation, personal/sick days
* Ability to work in person and remotely

**To apply, please send cover letter and resume to careers@jcrcny.org.**

Job Type: Full-time

Pay: $70,000.00 - $80,000.00 per year

Work Location: In person
